{"chunk_id":"consumer_mediation_rules_2020_hi_en:instrument-1:rule-1","heading":"1. Short title and commencement.—(1) These rules may be called the Consumer Protection","metadata":{"act":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","audit_status":"pending_human_review","chunk_scan_review_required":false,"chunking_strategy":"gazette_rules_en","document_ocr_used":false,"document_type":"rules","effective_from":"2020-07-20","effective_to":null,"gazette_reference":"G.S.R. 450(E)","instrument_index":1,"instrument_title":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","jurisdiction":"India","language":"en","modifies_source_ids":[],"ocr_pages":[],"ocr_used":false,"official_landing_url":"https://consumeraffairs.gov.in/pages/consumer-protection-acts","official_url":"https://consumeraffairs.gov.in/public/upload/files/Mediation%20Rules_1732703912.pdf","page_extraction":[{"alphanumeric_character_count":2337,"non_whitespace_character_count":2487,"ocr_used":false,"page_number":3,"status":"digital_text"}],"parser":"pymupdf","parser_requested":"auto","priority":3,"publication_date":"2020-07-15","relationship":"principal","retrieved_at":"2026-07-12T23:33:05.342040+00:00","review_note":null,"scan_review_pages":[],"scan_review_required":false,"sha256":"03e1a2b838afd37f1df5cec8cb10bed9256cb3bb8e9509fd7328c15ce089ae48","source_language":"hi-en","status":"in_force","target_instrument_title":null,"title":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","translation_available_in_source":true},"page_end":3,"page_start":3,"section_id":"1","source_id":"consumer_mediation_rules_2020_hi_en","text":"1.\nShort title and commencement.—(1) These rules may be called the Consumer Protection\n(Mediation) Rules, 2020.\n(2) They shall come into force on the 20th day of July, 2020."}
{"chunk_id":"consumer_mediation_rules_2020_hi_en:instrument-1:rule-2","heading":"2. Definitions—(1) ln these rules, unless the context otherwise requires,—","metadata":{"act":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","audit_status":"pending_human_review","chunk_scan_review_required":false,"chunking_strategy":"gazette_rules_en","document_ocr_used":false,"document_type":"rules","effective_from":"2020-07-20","effective_to":null,"gazette_reference":"G.S.R. 450(E)","instrument_index":1,"instrument_title":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","jurisdiction":"India","language":"en","modifies_source_ids":[],"ocr_pages":[],"ocr_used":false,"official_landing_url":"https://consumeraffairs.gov.in/pages/consumer-protection-acts","official_url":"https://consumeraffairs.gov.in/public/upload/files/Mediation%20Rules_1732703912.pdf","page_extraction":[{"alphanumeric_character_count":2337,"non_whitespace_character_count":2487,"ocr_used":false,"page_number":3,"status":"digital_text"}],"parser":"pymupdf","parser_requested":"auto","priority":3,"publication_date":"2020-07-15","relationship":"principal","retrieved_at":"2026-07-12T23:33:05.342040+00:00","review_note":null,"scan_review_pages":[],"scan_review_required":false,"sha256":"03e1a2b838afd37f1df5cec8cb10bed9256cb3bb8e9509fd7328c15ce089ae48","source_language":"hi-en","status":"in_force","target_instrument_title":null,"title":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","translation_available_in_source":true},"page_end":3,"page_start":3,"section_id":"2","source_id":"consumer_mediation_rules_2020_hi_en","text":"2.\n Definitions—(1) ln these rules, unless the context otherwise requires,—\n(a)\n\"Act\" means the Consumer Protection Act, 2019 (35 of 2019);\n(b)\n “Commission” means District Commission, State Commission or National Commission, as\nthe case may be;\n(c)\n“mediation cell” means a consumer mediation cell established in accordance with the\nprovisions of  section 74;\n(d)\n“panel” means a panel of mediators prepared by the Commission under sub-section (1) of\nsection 75;\n(e)\n “Parties” means parties to a dispute;\n(f)\n“Settlement\" means a settlement arrived at in the course of mediation.\n(2)  All other words and expressions used in the rules and not defined but defined in the Consumer\nProtection Act, 2019 (35 of 2019) shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in the Act."}
{"chunk_id":"consumer_mediation_rules_2020_hi_en:instrument-1:rule-3","heading":"3. Mediation Cell.---(1) Every Mediation Cell set up in a Commission, shall have a panel of mediators","metadata":{"act":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","audit_status":"pending_human_review","chunk_scan_review_required":false,"chunking_strategy":"gazette_rules_en","document_ocr_used":false,"document_type":"rules","effective_from":"2020-07-20","effective_to":null,"gazette_reference":"G.S.R. 450(E)","instrument_index":1,"instrument_title":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","jurisdiction":"India","language":"en","modifies_source_ids":[],"ocr_pages":[],"ocr_used":false,"official_landing_url":"https://consumeraffairs.gov.in/pages/consumer-protection-acts","official_url":"https://consumeraffairs.gov.in/public/upload/files/Mediation%20Rules_1732703912.pdf","page_extraction":[{"alphanumeric_character_count":2337,"non_whitespace_character_count":2487,"ocr_used":false,"page_number":3,"status":"digital_text"}],"parser":"pymupdf","parser_requested":"auto","priority":3,"publication_date":"2020-07-15","relationship":"principal","retrieved_at":"2026-07-12T23:33:05.342040+00:00","review_note":null,"scan_review_pages":[],"scan_review_required":false,"sha256":"03e1a2b838afd37f1df5cec8cb10bed9256cb3bb8e9509fd7328c15ce089ae48","source_language":"hi-en","status":"in_force","target_instrument_title":null,"title":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","translation_available_in_source":true},"page_end":3,"page_start":3,"section_id":"3","source_id":"consumer_mediation_rules_2020_hi_en","text":"3.\nMediation Cell.---(1) Every Mediation Cell set up in a Commission, shall have a panel of mediators\non the recommendation of a selection committee consisting of the President and a member of that\nCommission.\n(2)\nThe Mediation Cell shall have such support staff as may be decided by the President of\nthat Commission in consultation with the concerned Government and that Government shall provide\nall administrative assistance and infrastructure facilities required by the Commission"}
{"chunk_id":"consumer_mediation_rules_2020_hi_en:instrument-1:rule-4","heading":"4. Matters not to be referred to mediation.---The following matters shall not be referred","metadata":{"act":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","audit_status":"pending_human_review","chunk_scan_review_required":false,"chunking_strategy":"gazette_rules_en","document_ocr_used":false,"document_type":"rules","effective_from":"2020-07-20","effective_to":null,"gazette_reference":"G.S.R. 450(E)","instrument_index":1,"instrument_title":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","jurisdiction":"India","language":"en","modifies_source_ids":[],"ocr_pages":[],"ocr_used":false,"official_landing_url":"https://consumeraffairs.gov.in/pages/consumer-protection-acts","official_url":"https://consumeraffairs.gov.in/public/upload/files/Mediation%20Rules_1732703912.pdf","page_extraction":[{"alphanumeric_character_count":2337,"non_whitespace_character_count":2487,"ocr_used":false,"page_number":3,"status":"digital_text"},{"alphanumeric_character_count":995,"non_whitespace_character_count":1049,"ocr_used":false,"page_number":4,"status":"digital_text"}],"parser":"pymupdf","parser_requested":"auto","priority":3,"publication_date":"2020-07-15","relationship":"principal","retrieved_at":"2026-07-12T23:33:05.342040+00:00","review_note":null,"scan_review_pages":[],"scan_review_required":false,"sha256":"03e1a2b838afd37f1df5cec8cb10bed9256cb3bb8e9509fd7328c15ce089ae48","source_language":"hi-en","status":"in_force","target_instrument_title":null,"title":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","translation_available_in_source":true},"page_end":4,"page_start":3,"section_id":"4","source_id":"consumer_mediation_rules_2020_hi_en","text":"4.\n Matters not to be referred to mediation.---The following matters shall not be referred\nto mediation, namely:—\n(a) the matters relating to proceedings in respect of medical negligence resulting in grievous injury\nor death;\n(b) matters which relate to defaults or offences for which applications for compounding of offences\nhave been made by one or more parties;\n(c) cases involving serious and specific allegations of fraud, fabrication of documents, forgery,\nimpersonation, coercion;\n(d) cases relating to prosecution for criminal and non-compoundable offences;\n(e) cases which involve public interest or the interest of numerous persons who are not parties\nbefore the Commission:\nProvided that, in any case other than those mentioned in this rule, the Commission before\nwhich the case is pending may choose not to refer it to mediation if it appears to the\nCommission that no elements of a settlement exist which may be acceptable to the parties or that\nmediation is otherwise not appropriate having regard to the circumstances of the case and the\nrespective positions of the parties.\n\n4"}
{"chunk_id":"consumer_mediation_rules_2020_hi_en:instrument-1:rule-5","heading":"5. Refund of fee.—Where the Commission refers the parties to mediation, the complainant shall be","metadata":{"act":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","audit_status":"pending_human_review","chunk_scan_review_required":false,"chunking_strategy":"gazette_rules_en","document_ocr_used":false,"document_type":"rules","effective_from":"2020-07-20","effective_to":null,"gazette_reference":"G.S.R. 450(E)","instrument_index":1,"instrument_title":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","jurisdiction":"India","language":"en","modifies_source_ids":[],"ocr_pages":[],"ocr_used":false,"official_landing_url":"https://consumeraffairs.gov.in/pages/consumer-protection-acts","official_url":"https://consumeraffairs.gov.in/public/upload/files/Mediation%20Rules_1732703912.pdf","page_extraction":[{"alphanumeric_character_count":995,"non_whitespace_character_count":1049,"ocr_used":false,"page_number":4,"status":"digital_text"}],"parser":"pymupdf","parser_requested":"auto","priority":3,"publication_date":"2020-07-15","relationship":"principal","retrieved_at":"2026-07-12T23:33:05.342040+00:00","review_note":null,"scan_review_pages":[],"scan_review_required":false,"sha256":"03e1a2b838afd37f1df5cec8cb10bed9256cb3bb8e9509fd7328c15ce089ae48","source_language":"hi-en","status":"in_force","target_instrument_title":null,"title":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","translation_available_in_source":true},"page_end":4,"page_start":4,"section_id":"5","source_id":"consumer_mediation_rules_2020_hi_en","text":"5. Refund of fee.—Where the Commission refers the parties to mediation, the complainant shall be\nentitled to receive full amount of application fee paid in respect of such complaint, if a settlement\nis reached between such parties."}
{"chunk_id":"consumer_mediation_rules_2020_hi_en:instrument-1:rule-6","heading":"6. Resort to arbitral or judicial proceedings.—The parties shall not initiate any arbitral or judicial","metadata":{"act":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","audit_status":"pending_human_review","chunk_scan_review_required":false,"chunking_strategy":"gazette_rules_en","document_ocr_used":false,"document_type":"rules","effective_from":"2020-07-20","effective_to":null,"gazette_reference":"G.S.R. 450(E)","instrument_index":1,"instrument_title":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","jurisdiction":"India","language":"en","modifies_source_ids":[],"ocr_pages":[],"ocr_used":false,"official_landing_url":"https://consumeraffairs.gov.in/pages/consumer-protection-acts","official_url":"https://consumeraffairs.gov.in/public/upload/files/Mediation%20Rules_1732703912.pdf","page_extraction":[{"alphanumeric_character_count":995,"non_whitespace_character_count":1049,"ocr_used":false,"page_number":4,"status":"digital_text"}],"parser":"pymupdf","parser_requested":"auto","priority":3,"publication_date":"2020-07-15","relationship":"principal","retrieved_at":"2026-07-12T23:33:05.342040+00:00","review_note":null,"scan_review_pages":[],"scan_review_required":false,"sha256":"03e1a2b838afd37f1df5cec8cb10bed9256cb3bb8e9509fd7328c15ce089ae48","source_language":"hi-en","status":"in_force","target_instrument_title":null,"title":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","translation_available_in_source":true},"page_end":4,"page_start":4,"section_id":"6","source_id":"consumer_mediation_rules_2020_hi_en","text":"6.   Resort to arbitral or judicial proceedings.—The parties shall not initiate any arbitral or judicial\nproceedings in respect of a matter which  is the subject-matter of the mediation and also when\nsuch  parties have expressly undertaken not to initiate any such proceeding."}
{"chunk_id":"consumer_mediation_rules_2020_hi_en:instrument-1:rule-7","heading":"7. Settlement agreement not to be discharged by death of party thereto.—(1) A settlement","metadata":{"act":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","audit_status":"pending_human_review","chunk_scan_review_required":false,"chunking_strategy":"gazette_rules_en","document_ocr_used":false,"document_type":"rules","effective_from":"2020-07-20","effective_to":null,"gazette_reference":"G.S.R. 450(E)","instrument_index":1,"instrument_title":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","jurisdiction":"India","language":"en","modifies_source_ids":[],"ocr_pages":[],"ocr_used":false,"official_landing_url":"https://consumeraffairs.gov.in/pages/consumer-protection-acts","official_url":"https://consumeraffairs.gov.in/public/upload/files/Mediation%20Rules_1732703912.pdf","page_extraction":[{"alphanumeric_character_count":995,"non_whitespace_character_count":1049,"ocr_used":false,"page_number":4,"status":"digital_text"}],"parser":"pymupdf","parser_requested":"auto","priority":3,"publication_date":"2020-07-15","relationship":"principal","retrieved_at":"2026-07-12T23:33:05.342040+00:00","review_note":null,"scan_review_pages":[],"scan_review_required":false,"sha256":"03e1a2b838afd37f1df5cec8cb10bed9256cb3bb8e9509fd7328c15ce089ae48","source_language":"hi-en","status":"in_force","target_instrument_title":null,"title":"Consumer Protection (Mediation) Rules, 2020","translation_available_in_source":true},"page_end":4,"page_start":4,"section_id":"7","source_id":"consumer_mediation_rules_2020_hi_en","text":"7.  Settlement agreement not to be discharged by death of party thereto.—(1) A settlement\nagreement shall not be discharged by the death of any party thereto and shall be enforceable by or\nagainst the legal representative of the deceased party.\n(2) Nothing in this rule shall affect the operation of any law by virtue of which any right of action is\nextinguished by the death of a person.\n[F. No. J-10/2/2020-CPU]\nAMIT MEHTA, Jt. Secy.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nUploaded by Dte. of Printing at Government of India Press, Ring Road, Mayapuri, New Delhi-110064\nand Published by the Controller of Publications, Delhi-110054. MANOJ\nKUMAR VERMA\nDigitally signed by MANOJ\nKUMAR VERMA\nDate: 2020.07.16 18:03:38\n+05'30'"}
